Why Java's String has the method length() rather than property length (like an array?)

Because length() is defined in CharSequence interface, which is implemented by String. Interfaces can't define
properties in Java. Also, this makes it more interchangeable with other types

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26828405/why-javas-string-has-the-method-length-rather-than-property-length-like-an-a